When is the deadline for the internship position? I have two suggestions for you;

1. I think your first shot and your trapeze shot are your two strongest shots, I hope you don't mind but I also saw your modelling reel and your blue bat is very cute! Might I suggest that for AKA, they love to see people with more than one skill - the nature of small studios means you might need to bounce around onto different jobs from time to time, so being multi-skilled is a big asset. I'd suggest making a reel that includes only your best anim, plus some of the best of your other work too ^^
2. My second suggestion is about our work together, either now or at a time that works better for you, perhaps once your film is finished? I'd like to propose a few practice animations we can work through together to strengthen up your body mechanics and fundamentals. How does this sound for you? It may sound like a step back to go back to walk cycles and simpler shots, but I've found that every time I've taken a step back to go to the basics again, I've learnt so much more than I could've imagined. Walk cycles are one of my favourite things for this reason - you think you know  how to do them until you're asked to do another one and then you learn so much more than you thought possible!
